Totally fair — let’s make it super simple and avoid complex PATCH ops.

Goal

Add/update per-agent status under:

agentProcessing → agents → <agentId> → { stages..., overall..., agentInfo... }

…without changing your Cosmos DB trigger.

Easiest safe pattern (read → modify JSON → replace with ETag)
	1.	Read the doc (get ETag).
	2.	In memory (Jackson), create the missing nodes for agentProcessing/agents/<agentId>.
	3.	Set/update just the fields you need (for that agent).
	4.	Replace the document with If-Match ETag.
	5.	If you get 412, retry a few times.

Drop-in helpers

import com.azure.cosmos.*;
import com.azure.cosmos.models.*;
import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.JsonNode;
import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.node.ObjectNode;
import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.node.JsonNodeFactory;
import java.time.Instant;

private static String sanitizeKey(String arn){
    if (arn == null) return "";
    String s = arn.replace("/", "_").replace("\\","_").replace("#","_").replace("?", "_").trim();
    if (s.length() > 64) s = s.substring(0, 55) + "_H" + Integer.toHexString(s.hashCode());
    return s;
}

/** Super simple: read-modify-replace with ETag retry */
public static void upsertAgentStageSimple(
        CosmosContainer container,
        String correlationId,
        String rawAgentId,
        java.util.function.Consumer<ObjectNode> perAgentUpdater  // you set fields for this agent here
) {
    final int MAX = 5;
    CosmosException last = null;
    String agentKey = sanitizeKey(rawAgentId);

    for (int i = 0; i < MAX; i++) {
        try {
            // 1) read
            CosmosItemResponse<JsonNode> read = container.readItem(
                    correlationId, new PartitionKey(correlationId), JsonNode.class);
            String etag = read.getResponseHeaders().get("etag");
            ObjectNode doc = (ObjectNode) read.getItem();

            // 2) create parents if missing (in-memory only)
            ObjectNode agentProcessing = doc.with("agentProcessing");          // creates if missing
            ObjectNode agents          = agentProcessing.with("agents");       // creates if missing
            ObjectNode agentNode       = agents.with(agentKey);                // creates if missing

            // 3) hand control to your tiny updater (only touches this agent node)
            perAgentUpdater.accept(agentNode);

            // optional meta bump
            doc.with("meta").put("updatedAtUtc", Instant.now().toString());

            // 4) replace with ETag (optimistic concurrency)
            CosmosItemRequestOptions opts = new CosmosItemRequestOptions().setIfMatchETag(etag);
            container.replaceItem(doc, correlationId, new PartitionKey(correlationId), opts);
            return; // success

        } catch (CosmosException cx) {
            last = cx;
            if (cx.getStatusCode() == 412) { // ETag mismatch → retry
                try { Thread.sleep(Math.min(1000, 50 * (1 << i))); } catch (InterruptedException ignored) {}
                continue;
            }
            throw cx;
        }
    }
    throw last != null ? last : new RuntimeException("Cosmos replace failed after retries");
}

How to use (tiny one-liners per stage)
	•	Allow check OK

upsertAgentStageSimple(container, correlationId, arn, agent -> {
    agent.with("stages").with("allowCheck")
         .put("status", "OK")
         .put("at", Instant.now().toString());
    agent.put("updatedAtUtc", Instant.now().toString());
    agent.with("overall").put("status", "IN_PROGRESS");
});

